  "prompt": "What do you think of the BHIM app?",
  "response": "BHIM (Bharat Interface for Money) is a mobile payment app developed by the National Payments Corporation of India (NPCI) to facilitate digital transactions and promote cashless payments in India. Here are some key points about the app:\n\nPros:\n1. Easy to use interface\n2. Supports UPI (Unified Payments Interface) transactions\n3. Free to download and use\n4. Enables quick money transfers\n5. Helps promote digital payments in India\n\nCons:\n1. Limited to Indian users and bank accounts\n2. May have occasional technical glitches\n3. Requires smartphone and internet connection\n\nOverall, BHIM is considered a useful app for digital payments in India, particularly after demonetization and the push towards a cashless economy. However, individual user experiences may vary.",
